702139f-a.title: Bronx: Westchester Square - Fink Avenue
702139f-a.text:
63 and 65 Westchester Square, east side, between Fink and Ponton Avenues. No. 63 is the James Butler store.
About 1913
702139f-a.folder: Westchester Square & Fink Avenue, Bronx, NY

700944f-a.text:
East Tremont Ave., east side, south from Fink to Westchester Aves. The G.W. Bromley map of 1927 designates the above houses with the numbers 70 to 80,on what appears to be Westchester Square. A portion of the elevated structure of the I.R.T. Pelham Bay Park
subway line is visible on the extreme right.
August 25, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
